e public has been growing too. This unfortunately forced us to start with adding rules to the board.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
When you post on the Erollisi Marr EzBoard after the day/time this post has been written you agree with these new rules.<br>
<br>
<br>
You are a guest, act like one.<br>
<br>
1) If you start a flame thread in any other forum than <A href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes>Rants and Flames</a>, the administrator or moderators will move it to the &quot;right&quot; forum or just delete it (up to us). Continue with breaking the rule and you will get banned (no warnings, we ban you whenever we please).<br>
<br>
2) If you reply with a flame in any other forum than <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes>Rants and Flames</a>, the administrator or moderators will delete it. Continue with breaking the rule and you will get banned (no warnings, we ban you whenever we please).<br>
<br>
3) Anonymous flaming is NEVER allowed. If you flame anonymous your posts will be deleted and you might find yourself banned (read “banishment”)<br>
<br>
4) Mule EzBoard accounts are NOT allowed. Your EzBoard accounts created to flame people will get banned (read “banishment”) including all the other accounts that has been used by you. If nobody knows who you are, and you are only known to flame people you will fall into this category. The administrator and moderators may judge for their own if your account is a mule EzBoard account or not.<br>
<br>
5) Anything deemed sexually or racially discriminating, or of an equally offensive nature may get deleted and the administrator and moderators may also choose to ban the author (depends on the post).<br>
<br>
6) Adult material is NOT allowed. Pornographic stories, pictures, violent stories, etc. are NOT allowed. Post them and they will get deleted. Continue with breaking the rule and you will get banned (no warnings, we ban you whenever we please).<br>
<br>
7) The administrator and moderators are allowed to delete and modify posts/threads and/or ban you without giving you, or anyone else, an explanation.<br>
<br>
8) The administrator and moderators may add/change/remove rules whenever they please. When you post after these changes you agree with these new rules.<br>
<br>
9) Forums may have specific rules. If you post in those forums you agree with those rules.<br>
<br>
10) The administrator and moderators are allowed to “close” a thread whenever they please. They don't have to give you or anyone else an explanation. If you try to continue the “closed” thread with creating a new thread, this thread will be deleted. Continue with breaking the rule and you will get banned (no warnings, we ban you whenever we please).<br>
<br>
11) Re-submitting of deleted post (does not matter if you're the author or not) will get you banned (read “banishment”).<br>
<br>
12) Do not use offensive usernames and/or pictures. This will get you banned (read “banishment”).<br>
<br>
13) Size of personal pictures and signatures are restricted. Please read: <A href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrmessageboardrules.showMessage?topicID=5.topic>Rules of personal pictures & signature size</a>. If your personal picture and/or signature is larger than allowed, your posts may get deleted. So please, pay attention.<br>
<br>
14) If you post in the forums <A href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes>Rants and Flames</a> or <A href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrscammeralert>Scammer Alert</a>, you have to sign the posts with your in-game character name (read rule #3 for more information!). If your ezboard account is named after it, this is not necessary of course. For your info, the name of your level 3 twink camped in Freeport will not suffice, if you flame someone and this other person doesn’t know who you are and requests for a deletion of the post, it’ll be considered an anonymous flame and therefore will be deleted. And as always, when you continue the idiocy, you'll get banned (read “banishment”). <br>
<br>
15) Creating multiple accounts to back your own posts up under another name is not only very lame, it’s also not allowed. The posts will get deleted, and if you continue, you might find yourself banned (read “banishment”) eventually. Remember, the administrator and moderators are allowed to publicize your IP address, and/or any related information.<br>
<br>
16) If your post contains (private) information that was gathered from a non-public place, then you will find your post deleted. It speaks for itself that rule #11 applies here as well.<br>
<br>
17) Do not use pictures from a host that you do not control (i.e. 3rd party). We will not force you to change the picture (unless we receive complaints from the host), however, if the host of the picture decides to change it onto something inappropriate and against the rules of this board, you will have to carry the consequences. As rule #12 already says; the use of offensive/pornographic pictures in your signature, personal picture or personal icon will get you banned (read “banishment”).<br>
<br>
18) Auctions for real cash are not permitted on these boards. Such auctions will get deleted, and you're risking losing your posting rights (in other words: your sorry ass will be banned. read “banishment”).<br>
<br>
<br>
Banishment<br>
<br>
Since you can swap from ISP (and thus IP address) in an eyewink we have added a few rules.<br>
<br>
1) The administrator and moderators are allowed to do everything to get you banned from this board. Not only may they ban your IP, but they are also allowed to publicize your IP address (and all the other information you provided us with when you became a registered member on this board) that allows people to write complains to your ISP (Internet Service Provider).<br>
<br>
2) The administrator and moderators are allowed to write all your information (IP address, other EzBoard accounts, the guild you’re in) on the board so other people can prevent that you will be ruining their board also.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I hope everyone understand why we added these rules. Have fun...<br>
